Solution. We will calculate the required curvature using formula (3.3). First, we find the first and second derivatives of the implicit function $x^{2}+y^{2}-25=0$. Differentiating, we get:

$$
\begin{gathered}
2 x+2 y y^{\prime}=0, y^{\prime}=-\frac{x}{y} \\
y^{\prime \prime}=\left(-\frac{x}{y}\right)^{\prime}=-\frac{x^{\prime} y-x y^{\prime}}{y^{2}}=-\frac{y-x\left(-\frac{x}{y}\right)}{y^{2}}=-\frac{x^{2}+y^{2}}{y^{3}}=-\frac{25}{y^{3}}
\end{gathered}
$$

Substituting the obtained expressions into formula (3.3), we find

$$
k=\frac{\left|-\frac{25}{y^{3}}\right|}{\left[1+\left(-\frac{x}{y}\right)^{2}\right]^{\frac{3}{2}}}=\frac{25}{\left(x^{2}+y^{2}\right)^{\frac{3}{2}}}=\frac{25}{25^{\frac{3}{2}}}=\frac{1}{5}, k=\frac{1}{5}
$$

Therefore, the curvature of the given line is constant.

